  "abstract": "You must have heard the term \"She's not just a pretty face.\"? This term can also be applied to\r\nthe lovely marigold flower, which is not just beautiful to look at, but is also a useful diagnostic\r\ntool where Botrytis grey mold is concerned.\r\nBotrytis grey mold (BGM) is a disease, caused by the fungus Botrytis cinerea, that mainly\r\nattacks the reproductive structures of plants, especially the chickpea plant. Flower abortion is\r\na common symptom of the disease. The disease remains undiscovered until the signs of\r\ndamage become visible on the flower canopy (Fig. A). As a result, fungicides cannot be\r\napplied early enough to control the disease...........\r\n",
